query: What are the aerial tramways operating in Bettmeralp? Summarize the basic information of these aerial tramways.

The Betten Village-Bettmeralp tramway was built between 1951 to 1967 and 1979 with an elevation difference of 732 meters, a slope length of 1610 meters and a capacity of 500 persons per hour.
